art of a summary or risk assessment instead and keep \\\"agent_guidance\\\" empty. That's a clearer approach!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"hoplite-core is a pure Kotlin configuration library; the resolved artifact only needs its normal transitive Kotlin/coroutines dependencies, and meaningful coverage is reachable with built-in MapPropertySource or Java properties without Docker, extra Maven modules, or required environment/system properties.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Documentation examples often use YAML, JSON, TOML, or HOCON, but those formats require optional hoplite-* parser modules; they are not required for hoplite-core coverage and should not be added unless tests intentionally target those modules.\",\n    \"Hoplite 3 applies EnvironmentVariablesPropertySource by default, so tests using ConfigLoaderBuilder.default() may see ambient CI environment variables; deterministic tests can avoid this by using explicit property sources or an empty builder.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_06b2636db763525c016a3f490b19088194acdcc9705d248545\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2100, "output": 707, "cacheRead": 36352, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 39159, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782532353553, "responseId": "resp_06b2636db763525c016a3f49021bf08194b0bd021078dc8e62"}}
